        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/frank_murray_iii/{size}/301348_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-10-21T18:57:05.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Ikka, thanks for taking the time to document and post these wines.  Appreciate it very much.</p>\n<p>Did you consider putting in the Marguet Crayeres?  It\u2019s about 3/4ths Chardonnay, which makes it unique to the Egly.  It would not have met your intent to do PN so maybe this is why you might not have considered it.  And your comment about the Egly is interesting, as based on what I have read about Egly\u2019s style, the approach is to lower the pressure on those bottles so the wine is more to the fore than the bubbles.  Fascinating.</p>",
